      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GLORIA KEEPING (6) has an excellent record over this course and distance having never missed the placings in five starts, including three wins and two placings. Scored by 6 lengths last time (29.22) in a Grade 5 over 520m at Nowra. Makes strong appeal on best. RIPPER JOE (1) is struggling to break through but racing consistently, finishing in the minors three starts on end. Last time out flew the lids with a fast early sectional but gathered in and finished in the minors when second (29.81) at this track over 520m. Expected to feature. ZIPPING SMEE (2) was in the placings last time but shapes well for this on his powerful win the start prior, getting around Nowra over 520m in 29.64. Rates a leading chance if runs up to recent winning time. CYCLONE ETHICS (3) must be respected despite an unplaced effort here most recently.",
